          <declname>srv</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Manually turn the light off. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Instructs the controlled Lightness Server to turn the light off (Standby state). Calling this function temporarily disables occupancy sensor triggering (referred to as &quot;manual mode&quot; in the documentation). The server will remain in manual mode until the manual mode timer expires, see <verbatim>embed:rst:inline :kconfig:`CONFIG_BT_MESH_LIGHT_CTRL_SRV_TIME_MANUAL` </verbatim>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">srv</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Light Lightness Control Server instance.</para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<parameterlist kind="retval"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>0</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The Light Lightness Control Server was successfully turned off. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>-EBUSY</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The Light Lightness Control Server is disabled. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
